<p>In the latest development, Israel’s Defense Ministry liaison COGAT said Thursday that preparations to open the Rafah crossing with Egypt “for the movement of people only” are underway, with the opening date to be announced after coordination with Cairo [france24.com#1][dw.com#1][timesofisrael.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]. Officials emphasized that humanitarian aid continues to enter Gaza through other crossings while talks proceed over Rafah’s procedures [france24.com#1][timesofisrael.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]. On Wednesday, aid trucks rolled into Gaza after a dispute over the return of bodies of deceased prisoners was paused, helping stabilize a fragile truce [japantoday.com#1][dawn.com#1]. The United Nations urged Israel to open more crossings to expand aid access as negotiations continue [france24.com#1][dawn.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/O0ZITUBxtyjmboYwm7DgOJ0OAVD_zUkSn5AR5MtDjBO330NBctMn-bcxvPOQ4RMJ4qTddh5dAXGvz5tPAj2fVP_sUs0WdwqDzXPvV47y_nJ_' alt='Palestinians queue at a charity kitchen in Nuseirat camp, central Gaza Strip, October 15.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Planned aid scale: An Israeli official said 600 aid trucks would be allowed in, signaling a significant uptick in relief deliveries once procedures are finalized [dawn.com#1].</li><li>Ceasefire phases: Israel says the next stage of the truce requires Hamas to disarm and cede power, terms Hamas has so far rejected, while longer-term governance and stabilization arrangements remain undecided [dawn.com#1].</li><li>US warning: President Trump said he would consider allowing Israeli forces to resume fighting if Hamas fails to uphold the ceasefire he brokered [dawn.com#1].</li><li>Who can cross: Preparations specifically aim to open Rafah to Gazan citizens, according to an Israeli security official cited in reporting on the talks [dawn.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>Israel will return to those streets as soon as I say the word. If Israel could go in and knock the crap of them, the